==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scarify
<hw>Scar"i*fy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Scarified</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Scarifying</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F.
<ets>scarifier</ets>, L. <ets>scarificare</ets>, <ets>scarifare</ets>,
fr. Gr. <?/ to scratch up, fr. <?/ a pointed instrument.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>To scratch or cut the skin of; esp. <fld>(Med.)</fld>,
to make small incisions in, by means of a lancet or scarificator, so as
to draw blood from the smaller vessels without opening a large
vein.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Agric.)</fld> <def>To stir the surface soil of, as
a field.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scarious</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Scariose</ent>⟦br⟧
